## Key Techniques (PRIORITY ORDER)
# 1. PALM MUTING: Essential technique for authentic sound
#    - Difficulty: Intermediate
#    - Practice Notes: Rest palm lightly on bridge, maintain consistent pressure
#    - Common Mistakes: Too much palm pressure muffles strings completely
#    - Application: Used throughout main riff and rhythm sections

# 2. POWER CHORD PROGRESSIONS: Foundation of rhythm guitar parts
#    - Difficulty: Beginner to Intermediate
#    - Application: Chorus and verse sections
#    - Variations: Different inversions and voicings available

# 3. STRING BENDING: Lead guitar technique for solos
#    - Difficulty: Intermediate to Advanced
#    - Practice Notes: Focus on accurate pitch, use multiple fingers for support
#    - Application: Featured prominently in guitar solo section

